    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page, vertical scrolling application with a sticky top navigation. The structure is thematic, starting with a general overview ('Å to je Brilliant?'), moving to its pedagogical foundation, then to interactive practical examples (tabbed for Math/Informatics), key features, tools for educators (with a visualization), pros/cons, and finally practical details like pricing. This flow guides the user from the 'why' to the 'how', making the information digestible and more engaging than a linear report. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 1. Main Content -> Interactive Tabs: The core "Application in Teaching" section is split into 'Matematika' and 'Informatika' tabs. Goal: Organize dense, parallel information. Method: JS toggles content visibility. Justification: Prevents overwhelming the user with a long wall of text and allows them to focus on their subject of interest. 2. Educator Benefits -> Bar Chart (Chart.js): Visualizes the qualitative benefits mentioned for educators. Goal: Compare/Inform. Method: A horizontal bar chart with illustrative data. Justification: A chart provides a high-impact summary of the benefits, making them more memorable than a bulleted list. Library: Chart.js (Canvas). 3. Features/Pedagogy -> Icon-based Cards: Short text blocks with icons. Goal: Inform/Organize. Method: Tailwind CSS grid. Justification: Breaks down complex ideas into scannable, visually appealing chunks. NO SVG/Mermaid used. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
